protective_factors: Explicit denial of intent or plan.
Willingness to engage with current treatment plan and dose increase.
risk_factors: Severe symptoms of *Major Depressive Disorder, Recurrent, Moderate* (F33.1).
Active passive death ideation (Wish to be dead).
Lack of initial response to 4 weeks of *Sertraline*.
clinical_actions: Increased monitoring frequency is recommended following dose escalation.
Developed a concrete behavioral activation goal (10-minute walk).
Treated underlying depression with *Sertraline* dose increase.
